{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0096-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Module State and Cache Clearing",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1742313600000,
  "modified": 1774988061636,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hobson is a live programming environment. Editing any code item triggers "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "clearCache()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " in the module system, so the next "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "require()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " of any module re-evaluates it from scratch. Modules that store state in module-scoped variables (e.g. "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "let rendering = null"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") lose that state on re-evaluation. If another module calls "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "require('that-module')"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " after the cache is cleared, it gets a fresh module with null state."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Incident"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "keyboard-shortcuts called "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "require('viewport-manager').getRendering()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " inside the keydown handler to get the RenderingSystem. After any code item save triggered "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "clearCache()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", the re-required viewport-manager had "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "rendering = null"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". All keyboard shortcuts that needed "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "getViews()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " silently broke."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Fix and the Principle"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The fix was architectural, not defensive. The viewport layer follows a \"Bob\" pattern:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "A stateless boot listener (\"Bob\")"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " watches "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "kernel:boot-complete"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". This is viewport-manager. It creates the RenderingSystem and renders the initial viewport."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "The stateful object (RenderingSystem)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " persists for the lifetime of the page. It owns rendering, the registry, reactive subscriptions, etc."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Capabilities are passed via events, not require()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ". viewport-manager emits "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "viewport:ready"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " with closures ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "getViews"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "createElement"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "navigate"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ") that close over the live RenderingSystem. Consumers capture these at init time. No re-require needed."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Rules"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Never require() a stateful module at call time."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " After cache clear, you get a fresh module with null state. Capture what you need at init time instead."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Stateful modules should pass capabilities via events or API enrichment"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", not via exported getters that return module-scoped state."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "The kernel cannot create enriched APIs."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Enrichment is a viewport-layer concern. The kernel provides base APIs; the viewport layer adds rendering capabilities. Watch handlers that need rendering capabilities should watch "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "viewport:ready"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", not "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "kernel:boot-complete"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Remaining Work"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Several items still call "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "vpMgr.getRendering()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and are vulnerable to the same bug: test-runner-service, test-run-result-list-view, error-list handler ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "e7707000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "), and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "34237dbd"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". These should be migrated to receive capabilities via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "viewport:ready"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " or through the enriched API."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The deeper question: viewport-manager's "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "navigate()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "handlePopstate()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " also depend on module-scoped "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "rendering"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Moving navigation onto the RenderingSystem (or making viewport-manager truly stateless by passing rendering through closures) would complete the cleanup."
        }
      ]
    ],
    "tags": [
      "bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f",
      "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"
    ]
  },
  "attachments": []
}